modules.description: The module provides a foundation for handling tree structures through a set of related utilities. It includes types for nodes and trees, along with operations to construct, traverse, and manipulate tree elements. Functions such as `map`, `fold`, and `filter` allow for transformations and aggregations over tree data. Examples include building a binary tree and computing the sum of all node values.

Provides functions for parsing and processing import statements in OCaml code, including extracting module names and handling qualified references. Works with abstract syntax trees and source code strings generated by the ppx parser. Used to automate dependency tracking and module resolution during build processes.

Provides utilities for working with tree structures, including node and tree types, and operations like `map`, `fold`, and `filter` for transformation and aggregation. It supports constructing and traversing trees, enabling tasks such as building binary trees or calculating node value sums. Functions allow for recursive manipulation of hierarchical data. Examples include generating tree structures and performing depth-first traversals.
